 the number of joint detections that include an\noff-axis sGRB. We correct for this with a second, wider and weaker jet\ncomponent. We find that the majority of joint detections during the current era\nwill include an off-axis sGRB, making GRB170817A not as unlikely as one would\nthink. In the ET era, most joint detections will contain an on-axis sGRB.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Aug 2022 11:16:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-05"}
